The paper discusses the development of a novel deep learning approach for lung cancer detection using radiomics-driven methods. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves the analysis of medical images. The use of evolutionary deep intelligence also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of operational efficiency and patient privacy, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of evolutionary algorithms suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
